This paper is about a novel neural network architecture for machine comprehension tasks, which falls under the subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (ML), and thus cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of unstructured and structured datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be a relevant sub-category.
